<treatmentCitationGroup id="B4FD11C534147C31FEC0626CFDFF014A" box="[264,582,798,822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<treatmentCitation id="154C10FA34147C31FEC0626CFDFB014A" author="Malloch, J. R." box="[264,578,798,822]" page="17" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" year="1910">
<taxonomicName id="53ED4D6834147C31FEC0626CFDFB014A" authority="Malloch, 1910: 17" authorityName="Malloch" authorityPageNumber="17" authorityYear="1910" box="[264,578,798,822]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Beckerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A699EAF934147C31FEC0626CFECD0149" box="[264,372,799,822]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Beckerina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F07C4B1A34147C31FEB3626DFDFB014A" author="Malloch, J. R." box="[379,578,798,821]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="87 - 92" refId="ref13059" refString="Malloch, J. R. (1910) Scottish Phoridae, with tables of all the British species and notes of localities. Annals of Scottish Natural History, 1910, 15 - 21, 87 - 92." type="journal article" year="1910">Malloch, 1910: 17</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="945236EB34147C31FEC0621AFD7B0184" blockId="7.[264,1323,873,1019]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
The 
<typeStatus id="4B56884934147C31FEF5621AFED601FC" box="[317,367,873,899]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="53ED4D6834147C31FE14621AFC1F01FC" authority="(Becker, 1901)" baseAuthorityName="Becker" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[476,934,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Beckerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umbrimargo">
<emphasis id="A699EAF934147C31FE14621AFD5501FD" box="[476,748,873,898]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Beckerina umbrimargo</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F07C4B1A34147C31FD34621AFC2401FC" author="Becker, T." box="[764,925,873,899]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref11816" refString="Becker, T. (1901) Die Phoriden. Abhandlungen der zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 1, 1 - 100." type="journal article" year="1901">Becker, 1901</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, is the best­known species of the complex. The principal autapomorphies of this genus include a notopleural gland discharging by means of a duct whose fully exposed orifice is located at the front of each notopleuron of the male (N in 
<figureCitation id="0CD62A6E34147C31FDA46292FD0A0184" box="[620,691,993,1019]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="8.[264,383,1806,1830]" captionTargetBox="[347,1266,819,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-131@8.[324,1300,805,1802]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Beckerina umbrimargo male: (1) right wing; (2) left notopleuron and humerus (H = humerus, M = mesopleuron, N = opening of notopleural gland, S = spiracle, T = tegula). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030319" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030319/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DCF7656034147C3EFEC06542FC2C03D1" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="945236EB34147C31FEC06542FE550635" blockId="7.[264,1324,1073,1899]" box="[264,492,1073,1098]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="A699EAF934147C31FEC06542FE550635" box="[264,492,1073,1098]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Amended diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="945236EB34147C31FEF0652AFEDC0404" blockId="7.[264,1324,1073,1899]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
As indicated above, the diagnosis of this genus by 
<bibRefCitation id="F07C4B1A34147C31FC58652AFBDB060C" author="Borgmeier, T." box="[912,1122,1113,1139]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 256" refId="ref11968" refString="Borgmeier, T. (1963) Revision of the North American phorid flies. Part I. The Phorinae, Aenigmatiinae and Metopininae, except Megaselia (Diptera, Phoridae). Studia Entomologica, 6, 1 - 256." type="journal article" year="1963">Borgmeier (1963)</bibRefCitation>
is too broad and the amendments by 
<bibRefCitation id="F07C4B1A34147C31FDC965F2FD1306E4" author="Brown, B. V." box="[513,682,1153,1179]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="155 - 8" refId="ref12303" refString="Brown, B. V. (1997) The undescribed male of Beckerina sinefurca Borgmeier and the recognition of Neotropical Beckerina (Diptera: Phoridae). Entomological Problems, 28, 155 - 8." type="journal article" year="1997">Brown (1997)</bibRefCitation>
are of limited application by being knowingly geographically circumscribed. I suggest that the genus be restricted by excluding those whose males either lack notopleural glands or they have the orifice of their ducts concealed in a cleft; and by adding that both sexes retain the median furrow on the frons; the postpedicels are subglobose in both sexes and possess several SPS vesicles; labella have few spinules on their lower faces; palps with numerous medium sized bristles; abdominal tergites not extending full width of abdomen; the females lack Dufour’s crop mechanism; hairs below basal half of hind femur not differentiated from adjacent hairs of anterior face; hind tibia without or with only a single, dorsal, hair palisade; wing with vein 3 forked; vein Sc is well developed and its tip fuses with vein 1 (R1); the thin veins are brown; the costal cilia usually exceed 0.1 mm in length; costal index usually more than 0.5; membrane with dense microsetae, which are sometimes reduced in size; and axillary ridge with several bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="945236EB34147C3EFEF067FAFC2C03D1" blockId="7.[264,1324,1073,1899]" lastBlockId="8.[264,1322,284,430]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
This more restricted diagnosis is nearer that of 
<bibRefCitation id="F07C4B1A34147C31FC9367FAFB9104DC" author="Lundbeck, W." box="[859,1064,1673,1699]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref13037" refString="Lundbeck, W. (1922) Diptera Danica Part VI Pipunculidae, Phoridae. London, Wesley. 455 pp." type="book" year="1922">Lundbeck (1922)</bibRefCitation>
, but for allowing for a single hair palisade on the hind tibia and adding the notopleural gland character. Apart from the 
<typeStatus id="4B56884934147C31FEBC67AAFE1F048C" box="[372,422,1753,1779]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
species, this more restricted diagnosis means the genus retains 
<taxonomicName id="53ED4D6834147C31FB5967AAFA92048D" box="[1169,1323,1753,1778]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Beckerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmicola">
<emphasis id="A699EAF934147C31FB5967AAFA92048D" box="[1169,1323,1753,1778]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. burmicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below), 
<emphasis id="A699EAF934147C31FE6A6672FCE50565" box="[418,860,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName id="53ED4D6834147C31FE6A6672FDA10565" authorityName="Malloch" authorityYear="1919" box="[418,536,1793,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Beckerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteola">B. luteola</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="53ED4D6834147C31FDED6672FD710565" authorityName="Brues" authorityYear="1919" box="[549,712,1793,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Beckerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neotropica">B. neotropica</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="53ED4D6834147C31FD1E6672FCE50565" authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityYear="1969" box="[726,860,1793,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Beckerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setifrons">B. setifrons</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and probably other species that I have not examined. However, it excludes 
<taxonomicName id="53ED4D6834147C31FD74665AFBC8053C" authority="Borgmeier &amp; Prado" authorityName="Borgmeier &amp; Prado" authorityYear="1975" box="[700,1137,1833,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Beckerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequatoriana">
<emphasis id="A699EAF934147C31FD74665AFCC5053D" box="[700,892,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. aequatoriana</emphasis>
Borgmeier &amp; Prado
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="53ED4D6834147C31FBB6665AFD550514" authority="Enderlein" authorityName="Enderlein" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Beckerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="dominicana" variety="fuscohalterata">
<emphasis id="A699EAF934147C31FBB6665AFA93053D" box="[1150,1322,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. dominicana</emphasis>
Borgmeier, 
<emphasis id="A699EAF934147C31FE516622FDD00515" box="[409,617,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. fuscohalterata</emphasis>
Enderlein
</taxonomicName>
*, 
<taxonomicName id="53ED4D6834147C31FCC56622FBFB0514" authority="Borgmeier" authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityYear="1925" box="[781,1090,1873,1899]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Beckerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nudipleura">
<emphasis id="A699EAF934147C31FCC56622FC0D0515" box="[781,948,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. nudipleura</emphasis>
Borgmeier
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="53ED4D6834147C3EFB9C6622FED40349" authority="Malloch" authorityName="Malloch" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Beckerina" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orpnephiloides">
<emphasis id="A699EAF934147C31FB9C6622FA920515" box="[1108,1323,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. orpnephiloides</emphasis>
Malloch
</taxonomicName>
*, 
<taxonomicName id="53ED4D68341B7C3EFE40606FFD190349" authority="Borgmeier" authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityYear="1971" box="[392,672,284,310]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Beckerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilipleura">
<emphasis id="A699EAF9341B7C3EFE40606FFDA4034A" box="[392,541,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. pilipleura</emphasis>
Borgmeier
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="53ED4D68341B7C3EFD78606FFC7F0349" authority="(Schmitz)" baseAuthorityName="Schmitz" box="[688,966,284,310]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Beckerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polysticha">
<emphasis id="A699EAF9341B7C3EFD78606FFCF3034A" box="[688,842,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. polysticha</emphasis>
(Schmitz)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="53ED4D68341B7C3EFBC9606FFAA10349" authority="Borgmeier" authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityYear="1969" box="[1025,1304,284,310]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Brownphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinefurca">
<emphasis id="A699EAF9341B7C3EFBC9606FFB36034A" box="[1025,1167,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. sinefurca</emphasis>
Borgmeier
</taxonomicName>
*. Of these excluded species I have only examined specimens of those species marked with an asterisk. These I assign to new genera below. The rest I decline to allocate to other genera until slide mounted specimens have been examined.
</paragraph>
